transit: 5 min walk to Capitol Metro Rail (train that takes you downtown) and bus stops within a few minutes (the slowest form of transportation in Austin). B-cycle is a city operated bicycle rental company with several "stations" on the east side where you can rent bikes to get around. You're only 3 miles from Ladybird Lake Trail and bicycling to many parts of central Austin are easy and beautiful along this trail. Uber, Lyft and taxis are in high demand during ACL & SXSW so plan ahead if possible.
access: Several local restaurants, small clubs, music venues, convenience store and cafes within walking distance. Just 1.2 miles from downtown & the University of Texas, ~ 2 miles from the Austin Convention Center & ~ 5 miles from Zilker Park/Barton Springs (ACL location).

transit: The most popular form of transportation is Uber. Similar to a taxi service, but typically less expensive. Download the app to your phone and see how affordable it is! Austin’s bus system, Capitol Metro, costs only 1 per single ride or 2 for an all-­day pass. The number 5 (Woodrow/S 5th bus) picks up one block away at the corner of S. 5th and Mary and goes directly into downtown (a 10 minute ride). There are also routes that pick up on Lamar. Numerous other connections pick-­‐up at various locations throughout downtown.

transit: ******PLEASE NOTE LOCATION AND DISTANCE/TRAVEL TIMES BELOW.  ******MOST OF OUR GUESTS HAVE OR RENT CARS.  Downtown and Barton Springs are bikeable.  You can bike to SoCo, but there can be traffic and there is a long hill.  It's fast and easy to take one of the many rideshare options, including Uber and Lyft.  Rideshare to downtown is about 12 plus tip.  Pro tip:  rideshares mean you don't have to find a parking space!   Bike to downtown:  25-30 minutes (5 miles) Drive to downtown/SoCo area: 15 minutes (5-6 miles) Transport other than the bikes is recommended at night, but we do have lights.
access: We have a choice of bikes you may borrow (see photos.)  They are stored outside behind the cottage.  They were our bikes and we are 5'7" and 5'8".  Each bike has a lock and spare tube/repair kit and lights.  We have three helmets available.  Please walk the bikes through the cottage and take them in/out through the gate at the driveway, NOT through gate behind the cottage. Fast wifi, 37" flat screen TV with Roku, with streaming channels including Netflix, local TV channels.  Stereo with iPhone cable and CD player, propane and charcoal grill, picnic backpack. There is ample parking on the street, and you should be able to park in front of our house. Please DO NOT park in our driveway except for loading and unloading.

transit: There is plenty of free street parking in front of the house. Bus stops (17, 21, 22) and bike rental shops are very close by. Austin B-cycle is our bicycle sharing program, and there are many stations around town, the closest of which is a ten minute walk from our house. The fee is 12 per day or 15 for the weekend with unlimited use. Car2Gos and pedicabs are abundant in our neighborhood. We recommend supporting our local taxi drivers by using Austin Co-op Taxi. If you prefer rideshare apps, Ride Austin is a non-profit that has donated hundreds of thousands of dollars to local charities through riders rounding up their fare, and drivers get 100% of the fare.

transit: There are plenty of ways to get around Austin, with or without your own wheels: - Uber or Lyft for longer trips. - CapMetro (Austin's public transit system) is the easiest way to explore Downtown and the greater Austin area on the cheap. Single bus rides start at 1.25 (transfers not included), while day passes run as little as 2.50. You can buy tickets online, at most grocery stores, or through the CapMetro app, which also gives you up-to-date travel information. - For short trips (when sober), hop on one of the dockless electric scooters currently operating in Austin including LimeBike & Bird. - Had a few? Pedicabs can be an easy way to navigate Downtown at night and on the weekends and are best just hailed from the street. Most pedicab drivers prefer cash, but some take cards. - If you’re a lover of the two-wheeled lifestyle, Austin B-cycle, the city’s docked bike system, has more than 75 kiosks dotting Central Austin, one of which is located on 6th Street! transit: Public transit is not the greatest in Austin but there are plenty of restaurants and shops within walking distance of the apartment. You can also use any of the ride sharing companies in town pretty easily and it's affordable to get anywhere being so close to the center. There are also plenty of electric scooters and bikes scattered throughout the neighborhood. This is the recommended form of transport to get familiar with the area. If you're hiring a car, it is easily accessible by I-35 and Mopac (Loop 1).

transit: Plenty of parking at the Lake Travis Tree Lodge. Boat parking too. Also, the biggest public boat ramp on Lake Travis is right across the street from the Tree Lodge. There is not any public transportation options in this area. Uber operates in the Lake Travis area if you are going out here, but Austin kicked them out so you cannot take Uber into Austin anymore.
access: The Lake Travis Tree Lodge is accessed via an exterior stairway that is just for the guests. I live on the premises but the set up is closer to a duplex than a shared house. There are no shared spaces. Guests are welcome to enjoy the yard and the secluded, small two-street no-outlet neighborhood. The Lake Travis Tree Lodge has a digital entry keypad and each guest is given their own code.

transit: Walking is the number one benefit staying here but if you aren't in the mood to walk, car services are super cheap given the short distance. If you are out on Rainey or East 6th I love to take a Pedicab back home is also fun and usually under 10! For car service I recommend using FARE which you can download their app.  Bus stop is half a block down as well as around the corner.

transit: All major ride-share companies, like Lyft, Uber operate in Austin. We also have Ride Austin, a local ride share company, as well as Capital Metro public transit operating busses, paratransit services and a commuter rail system known as the Capital MetroRail.
access: There is driveway parking available for one car. Street parking is also fine. We utilize state-of-the-art door locks that create unique codes just for each guest's stay, and a full set of instructions with this code and more information is emailed to our guests about a week prior to reservation start date.

transit: Home is located just six miles from the airport. Public transit to downtown available 13 minutes walk from the house (0.6 mile).  Since the property is so close to downtown why not take Uber, Lyft or a taxi?  Car2Go also available 20 minutes walking distance (one mile). Since Austin is a large city geographically you may consider a car rental.  Home is 10 minute drive to famous 6th Street and downtown.

transit: *Don’t rent a car! Take the METRO bus for 1.75 per rider! Leaves every 30 minutes from baggage claim, takes a 20-30 minute drive and drops you off at 4th and Trinity, just 1 block from this property. Search: “Austin MetroAirport 100” for more info! *Need to get around during your stay? Sign up for Car2go prior to your trip (allow approx. 5-7 days). Becoming a member allows you to hop in any available Car2go 2-seater car and drive wherever you’d like for .41 cents per minute. Search: “Car2Go Austin” for more info! *Want to rent a bike during your trip to zip around Downtown or the beautiful Lady Bird Lake? Austin Bcycle offers 24/7 on-demand bicycle rental stations throughout Austin. There’s several within blocks of this unit! Search: “Austin Bcycle” for more info!
